View this page in a Web Browser

 

Meetup: Chatbots
becoming Virtual Digital
Assistants - The next
generation

 

Join this meetup and get introduced
to Digital Assistants, the future of
Chatbots, taking leverage of
Oracle’s latest Digital Assistant
platform.

 

Tuesday, June 18, 2019
18:30 - 20:30

 

 

Oracle Developer Meetup Porto

 

Every now and then there’s a paradigm change in how we interact with computers.

Chatbots have already conquered their own market place but, as usual, technology never ceases to amaze us!

Unlike a simple chatbot, a Virtual Digital Assistant can be equipped with multiple skills covering a wide set of domains and scenarios all from one conversational interface. There’s no need to have and separately orchestrate the appropriate chatbot that supports a specific service. DA’s will aim to be the single point of contact for all the conversational experiences.

The session will cover:

  • Product key concepts and features
  • Integrations & Channels
  • Custom development
  • Chat handover and hijack
  • As well as our knowledge and lessons learned on ongoing & production projects from an actual development team point of view.

 

 

 

 

Oracle Developer Meetup Porto

Tuesday, June 18, 2019
18:30 - 20:30		  
 

eProseed Portugal

Porto

Dear user,
 
Changing your password is a periodic mandatory procedure, according to the security policy in force.
 Your current password will expire in 2 days.
 
Please change the password before the date specified, by accessing the webpage  https://iam.kernelcars.com/change-password (available both for intranet and Internet). Otherwise, your acount will be blocked.
 
To unlock, you can:
 1. On a computer conected by cable to the Internet, on the logon screen, select «Switch User» and «Unlock Account / Password Change» and you will be directed to the IAM webpage where you can request password change or account unlock.
 2. Alternatively, you can access the IAM:
 2.1 From the computer of a coleague connected to the intranet to change your password or unlock the account.
 2.2 From any computer connected to the Internet to change your password or unlock the account.
 3. As a last resource, you can contact the Service Desk.
 
Regards,
Identity and Access Management (IAM)
